All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
App
For now, our app creates an HTTP server that can only get and add data.
Database  
Database.RowData
RowData is like a struct in C: we use it to hold data, and we allow direct access to its fields.
DataRow
DataRow holds a row of information.
DataRowLite
DataRowLite is for communicating back a subset of the information in a DataRow.
DataStore
DataStore provides access to a set of objects, and makes sure that each has a unique identifier that remains unique even after the object is deleted.
SimpleRequest
SimpleRequest provides a format for clients to present title and message strings to the server.
StructuredResponse
StructuredResponse provides a common format for success and failure messages, with an optional payload of type Object that can be converted into JSON.
